{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}{{Abortion in the Catholic Church}}[[File:Pochod pro zivot 2009.jpg|thumb|2009 Pro-life March on [[Wenceslas Square]], 28 March 2009]]
The '''March for Life''' ({{Lang-cs|Pochod pro život}}) is an annual [[anti-abortion movements|anti-abortion]] demonstration held in [[Prague]] in late March, close to the [[International Day of the Unborn Child]] (25 March). The first march was held in 2001. It is organized by ''{{lang|cs|Hnutí pro život}}'' (Pro-life Movement) of the [[Czech Republic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zpravy.ihned.cz/c1-23145395-prahou-projde-pruvod-na-protest-proti-potratum|title=Prahou projde průvod na protest proti potratům|date=24 March 2007|work=[[Hospodářské noviny]]|publisher=iHNED|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref> The participants usually carry white crosses symbolizing the victims of abortion.<ref name="rozhlas">{{cite web|url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/zpravy/politika/_zprava/prahou-proslo-1500-odpurcu-potratu-nesli-bile-krize-a-modlili-se--1036628|title=Prahou prošlo 1500 odpůrců potratů, nesli bílé kříže a modlili se|last=Königsmarková|first=Anna |author2=Kašpar, Mirko |date=24 March 2012|publisher=[[Czech Radio]]|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref> The event is supported by the [[Latin Church|Latin]] and [[Eastern Catholic Churches|Eastern Catholic]] churches. The march is usually opened by a [[Mass (Catholic Church)|Mass]] celebrated by [[Dominik Duka]], [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]]-[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Prague|Archbishop of Prague]].<ref name="rozhlas"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.proglas.cz/detail-clanku/prahou-prosel-pochod-pro-zivot.html|title=Prahou prošel Pochod pro život|last=Horáková|first=Helena|date=27 March 2011|publisher=Radio Proglas|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref> Politicians such as [[Pavel Bělobrádek]] ([[KDU-ČSL]]), [[Jitka Chalánková]] ([[TOP 09]]), Eva Richtrová ([[ČSSD]]) and Jaroslav Plachý ([[Civic Democratic Party (Czech Republic)|ODS]]) have attended the march in the past.<ref name="novinky">{{cite web|url=http://www.jihoceskenovinky.cz/zpravy/zpravy/prahou-prosel-pochod-pro-zivot-prisli-i-politici/|title=Prahou prošel Pochod pro život, přišli i politici |date=25 March 2013|work=Jihočeské novinky|publisher=jihoceskenovinky.cz|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref> The march leads to the [[Wenceslas Square]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tyden.cz/rubriky/domaci/proti-potratum-protestovala-v-praze-tisicovka-lidi_197483.html?showTab=nejctenejsi-24#.UxrOyc6qLXR|title=Proti potratům protestovala v Praze tisícovka lidí|date=26 March 2011|publisher=[[Týden]] (originally [[ČTK]])|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref> and ends at the [[Saint Wenceslas]] statue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ceskatelevize.cz/ct24/blogy/219732-potrinacte-ke-sv-vaclavu/|title=Potřinácté ke sv. Václavu|last=Peroutka jr.|first=Ferdinand|date=21 March 2013|publisher=[[Czech Television]] (blog)|language=Czech|accessdate=8 March 2014}}</ref>

