'''Potassium ascorbate''' is a [[Compound (chemistry)|compound]] with formula KC<sub>6</sub>H<sub>7</sub>O<sub>6</sub>. It is the [[potassium]] [[salt (chemistry)|salt]] of [[ascorbic acid]] ([[vitamin C]]) and a [[mineral ascorbate]].  As a food additive, it has [[E number]] E303, INS number 202. Although it is not a permitted [[food additive]] in the UK<ref>UK Food Standards Agency: {{cite web |url=http://www.food.gov.uk/safereating/chemsafe/additivesbranch/enumberlist |title=Current EU approved additives and their E Numbers |accessdate=2011-10-27}}</ref> or the USA, it is approved for use in Australia and New Zealand.<ref>Australia New Zealand Food Standards Code{{cite web |url=http://www.comlaw.gov.au/Details/F2011C00827 |title=Standard 1.2.4 - Labelling of ingredients |accessdate=2011-10-27}}</ref>

